Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.08,0:00:03.11,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Science fiction begins with Frankenstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.08,0:00:03.11,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,科幻始于《弗兰肯斯坦》
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.11,0:00:08.25,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,So many of the ideas, and the tropes, even the philosophy behind science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.11,0:00:08.25,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,科幻背后众多的思想、隐喻甚至是哲学
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:10.65,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,come from this one great work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:10.65,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,都来自这部伟大的作品
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.70,0:00:14.08,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,So let us start where we must, and talk Frankenstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.70,0:00:14.08,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,所以让我们就此开始，谈谈《弗兰肯斯坦》
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.14,0:00:20.60,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,( Music )
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.14,0:00:20.60,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,（ 音乐 ）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.62,0:00:24.34,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,The very first sentence of the preface to Frankenstein reads thus,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.62,0:00:24.34,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,《弗兰肯斯坦》的前言，开篇这样写道：
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.48,0:00:28.00,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"The event on which this fiction is founded, has been supposed, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.48,0:00:28.00,ExtraSciFi - 引用,,0,0,0,,“关于这部小说设定的背景，已经有人提出过猜想，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.03,0:00:31.46,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"by Dr. Darwin, and some of the physiological writers of Germany,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.03,0:00:31.46,ExtraSciFi - 引用,,0,0,0,,“比如达尔文博士和一些德国的生理学学者，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.51,0:00:33.87,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"as not of impossible occurrence.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.51,0:00:33.87,ExtraSciFi - 引用,,0,0,0,,“他们认为这并非不可能发生。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.96,0:00:36.97,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"I shall not be supposed as according the remotest degree of{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.96,0:00:36.97,ExtraSciFi - 引用,,0,0,0,,“我对于这样一种想象，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.97,0:00:39.12,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"serious faith to such an imagination,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.97,0:00:39.12,ExtraSciFi - 引用,,0,0,0,,“不会有丝毫当真，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.12,0:00:42.60,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"yet, in assuming it as the basis of a work of fancy,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.12,0:00:42.60,ExtraSciFi - 引用,,0,0,0,,"然而，尽管我以此为想象的基础，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.60,0:00:47.76,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"I have not considered myself as merely weaving a series of supernatural terrors."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.60,0:00:47.76,ExtraSciFi - 引用,,0,0,0,,“我并不觉得自己仅仅是在编造一系列超自然的恐怖故事。”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.82,0:00:52.09,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,And it is on that statement that all of science fiction is founded.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.82,0:00:52.09,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,所有科幻都是建立在这样一种观点之上的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.17,0:00:55.83,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Shelley is saying that the events in this book could be real,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.17,0:00:55.83,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,雪莱说，书中发生的事有可能成真
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.83,0:00:58.92,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,not that they are real or even that they are remotely likely,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.83,0:00:58.92,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,不是因为它们是真的，甚至几乎不可能发生
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.92,0:01:01.90,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,but they could exist in the universe we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.92,0:01:01.90,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,而是它们可能存在于我们所知的宇宙中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.95,0:01:05.40,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Eventually, we will escape the bounds of this statement with science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.95,0:01:05.40,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,我们最终会跳出科幻中这一观点的框架
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:06.79,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,but it's this idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:06.79,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,不过正是这样的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.79,0:01:11.40,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,the idea that our sci-fi tales exist within our rational world,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.79,0:01:11.40,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,即科幻故事是有可能存在于我们的理性世界的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.40,0:01:14.52,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,within the bounds of what science tells us is possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.40,0:01:14.52,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,并不违背科学规律
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:18.68,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that makes science fiction fundamentally different from fantasy or myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:18.68,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,使得科幻从根本上有别于奇幻和神话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.87,0:01:22.56,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,And that thought is incredibly important at the birth of the genre.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.87,0:01:22.56,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这一想法，对于科幻体裁的诞生至关重要
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.56,0:01:26.33,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,This is what separates it out as its own distinct literary branch
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.56,0:01:26.33,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这也让科幻开辟出独立的文学分支
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.33,0:01:28.66,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and allows it to have rules and conventions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.33,0:01:28.66,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,拥有自己的规则和惯例
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.66,0:01:34.46,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,unlike those already existing genres of the fantastic, of horror or folklore or myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.66,0:01:34.46,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,不同于已有的幻想体裁，诸如恐怖小说、民间传说或者神话故事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.55,0:01:37.79,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,It's also initially part of what gets us to buy in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.55,0:01:37.79,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这也是科幻最初吸引我们的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:42.17,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Science fiction uses the possible as a lens for our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.86,0:01:42.17,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,科幻以“可能成真之事”作为观察世界的透镜
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.26,0:01:44.83,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,It may be the remote and the unlikely,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.26,0:01:44.83,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,也许遥远或者不可能
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.83,0:01:47.68,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,but what better way to look at human nature
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.83,0:01:47.68,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,然而要想审视人性，有什么方法能比得上
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.68,0:01:52.90,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,than to set it against the extreme cases of what it might someday encounter
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.68,0:01:52.90,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,将其置于将来有可能发生的极端情形下
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:54.59,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and see what rolls out?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:54.59,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,然后看看会发生什么呢
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.67,0:01:56.62,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,This is so important to Shelley
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.67,0:01:56.62,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,雪莱觉得这一点极为重要
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.62,0:01:59.64,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that it's the very first thing that's presented to the reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.62,0:01:59.64,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,因此她一上来就将其揭示给读者
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.64,0:02:02.92,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Without this idea of the fantastic possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.64,0:02:02.92,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,没有“所想之事可能成真”的这样的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:05.28,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,I don't think we have science fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:05.28,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,我觉得就不会有科幻
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.36,0:02:09.48,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,But that is far from the only standard Frankenstein created for sci-fi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.36,0:02:09.48,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,不过《弗兰肯斯坦》为科幻创立的标准远不止于此
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.55,0:02:13.51,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Today, we are going to explore all the other ways that Frankenstein established.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.55,0:02:13.51,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,今天我们将探索《弗兰肯斯坦》建立的其他模式
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.51,0:02:18.27,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Tropes, styles, and techniques that we almost take for granted in sci-fi today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.51,0:02:18.27,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,隐喻、风格和技术，那些我们如今在科幻中视为理所当然的元素
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.42,0:02:21.53,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Now, before I tread any further, I should say one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.42,0:02:21.53,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,现在，在展开之前，我得说件事
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.60,0:02:24.23,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,if you only know this story from the movies,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.60,0:02:24.23,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,如果你只是从电影中了解到这个故事
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.23,0:02:26.83,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,you don't actually know this story at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.23,0:02:26.83,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,那么其实你对它一无所知
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.91,0:02:28.92,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,The films have little to do with the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.91,0:02:28.92,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,电影和原著关联甚少
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.92,0:02:32.08,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,And while it is actually a really worthwhile exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.92,0:02:32.08,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,尽管思考如下议题很有价值
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:35.53,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,to think about why this story has been interpreted and reimagined
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:35.53,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,即为什么这个故事被人以各种方式诠释和重新想象
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.56,0:02:37.68,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,the way it has throughout the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.56,0:02:37.68,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,贯穿了20世纪
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:41.18,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,everything I talk about today will be regarding the original work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.68,0:02:41.18,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,我今天的讨论都将只围绕原著
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.31,0:02:44.30,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,So let's start at the beginning, with a young man,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.31,0:02:44.30,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,所以让我们从一个年轻人开始
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.35,0:02:48.41,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,obsessed by alchemy and yet fascinated by the power of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.35,0:02:48.41,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他痴迷炼金术，也醉心于科学的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.47,0:02:51.42,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,A young man determined to overcome death
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.47,0:02:51.42,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他决意战胜死神
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.49,0:02:53.18,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,for the fame it might bring him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.49,0:02:53.18,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,追求随之而来的名誉
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.25,0:02:57.58,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,A young man blind to the consequences of what he is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.25,0:02:57.58,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.72,0:02:59.98,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about Victor Frankenstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.72,0:02:59.98,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,我们来谈谈维克多·弗兰肯斯坦
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.98,0:03:03.77,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Victor is the blueprint for the frustrated scientist trope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.98,0:03:03.77,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,维克多是无数失意科学家的原型
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.85,0:03:05.56,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,All of those other scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.85,0:03:05.56,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,所有其他的科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:10.52,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,you read about in comics, see in movies, or find in the pages of later science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:10.52,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,那些你在漫画、电影或者是后来的科幻小说中接触到的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:12.96,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,those who would have been so great for the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:12.96,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,如果世人没有埋没他们的天才
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.97,0:03:15.56,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,if the world had only acknowledged their genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.97,0:03:15.56,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他们本可以成为伟大的人物
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.56,0:03:18.81,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,They are all basically riffs on Victor Frankenstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.56,0:03:18.81,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,本质上他们都是维克多·弗兰肯斯坦的翻版
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.81,0:03:23.07,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,In fact, this has become so common and so ingrained into pop culture
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.81,0:03:23.07,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,事实上，这在流行文化中是如此普遍和深入人心
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.07,0:03:24.76,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that a lot of these characters pop up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.07,0:03:24.76,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,以至于无数类似的角色涌现出来
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:26.96,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,without their authors even really thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.78,0:03:26.96,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,而他们的作者甚至都没有真正思考过
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.96,0:03:29.63,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,the legacy of Victor Frankenstein that they come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.96,0:03:29.63,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,灵感来源——维克多·弗兰肯斯坦
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.79,0:03:32.99,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Victor is also our model of scientific hubris.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.79,0:03:32.99,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,维克多也是科学傲慢主义的典型
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.05,0:03:35.76,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,He believes that he can best death itself
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.05,0:03:35.76,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他相信自己能击败死神
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.76,0:03:38.40,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,by creating life out of the parts of the dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.76,0:03:38.40,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,方法是用死者的躯体碎块创造生命
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.50,0:03:41.53,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and thinking his own intellect to be so superior,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.50,0:03:41.53,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他觉得自己智力超群
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.53,0:03:45.40,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,he doesn't even once consider the ramifications of what he's doing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.53,0:03:45.40,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,因此甚至都没有考虑过所做之事的后果
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:46.84,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,until it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:46.84,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,直到为时已晚
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:49.44,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,He is the model for all of those characters
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:49.44,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他是因违背自然法则
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.44,0:03:51.71,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,punished for defying the laws of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.44,0:03:51.71,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,而受到惩罚的典型
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.79,0:03:54.92,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,for the scientist so obsessed with pursuing their ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.79,0:03:54.92,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,科学家对自己的想法是如此着迷
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.91,0:03:56.38,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that they don't even consider
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.91,0:03:56.38,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,以至于他们从未考虑过
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:59.43,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,what those ideas might ultimately mean for humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:59.43,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,对人类来说，这些想法最后意味着什么
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.52,0:04:01.32,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,But he's also a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.52,0:04:01.32,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,但他也是个懦夫
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.32,0:04:03.75,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,At the first sight of his own creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.32,0:04:03.75,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,一看到自己的造物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.75,0:04:06.20,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,he flees because it's physically deformed,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.75,0:04:06.20,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他就溜了，因为造物外表畸形
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:08.28,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,because it's too ugly to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:08.28,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,丑到无法直视
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.40,0:04:10.01,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,just the way he made it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.40,0:04:10.01,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,正是他创造时的样子
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.11,0:04:12.47,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,which brings us to the monster itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.11,0:04:12.47,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这也将我们引到怪物本身
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.53,0:04:16.79,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,An innocent, filled with gentle kindness and a love for the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.53,0:04:16.79,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他天真无邪，温和善良，热爱世界
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:20.17,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,who is rejected at every turn for his physical appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:20.17,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,却因外表丑陋，处处遭人排斥
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:22.81,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,eventually growing callus and cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:22.81,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,最终它变得冷酷无情
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.87,0:04:25.96,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,How many times in science fiction have we seen
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.87,0:04:25.96,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,在科幻中，我们是不是见过无数次
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.96,0:04:27.92,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,this monster with the heart of gold?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.96,0:04:27.92,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这样心地善良的怪物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.92,0:04:30.87,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,I present to you that trope's origins,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.92,0:04:30.87,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,我已经将这种隐喻的起源展示给你们了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.93,0:04:33.21,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and like many things in Frankenstein
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.93,0:04:33.21,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,并且就像《弗兰肯斯坦》中的许多事物一样
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.21,0:04:34.92,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Shelley explores this trope
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.21,0:04:34.92,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,雪莱对这一隐喻的探索
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.92,0:04:38.12,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,far more thoroughly than many who would eventually borrow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.92,0:04:38.12,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,远比许多后来者深刻
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.26,0:04:40.33,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,The monster, outwardly ugly,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.26,0:04:40.33,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,外表丑陋的怪物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:44.89,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,finds itself continuously rejected by an inwardly ugly humanity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:44.89,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,发现自己不断遭到内心丑陋的人类排斥
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.95,0:04:46.98,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,rejected at birth by Victor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.95,0:04:46.98,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,诞生时被维克多抛弃
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:49.28,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,attacked in the first village he visited,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.98,0:04:49.28,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,进入第一个村庄时受到攻击
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.28,0:04:52.01,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,turned away by the cottagers he cared for
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.28,0:04:52.01,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,被他喜欢的村民驱逐
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.08,0:04:55.93,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and thus, at last, the monster turns on humanity itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.08,0:04:55.93,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,因此，怪物终于开始仇视人类
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:57.87,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,This theme of rejection
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:57.87,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这一主题
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.87,0:05:02.27,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,despite offering the best intentions and offering something truly of worth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.87,0:05:02.27,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,即，尽管表示了最大的善意，奉献了真正宝贵的东西，却依旧遭人排斥
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:05.20,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,has become not only a theme of science fiction literature
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:05.20,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,不单单存在于科幻文学
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.20,0:05:07.89,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,but of the geek culture that has grown up around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.20,0:05:07.89,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,也存在于由其衍生的极客文化
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.10,0:05:10.97,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,But part of the reason that we see nobility in the monster
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.10,0:05:10.97,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,然而我们觉得这个怪物高尚，部分是出于
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.97,0:05:15.07,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,is that we see it self-educate, reading the greatest books of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.97,0:05:15.07,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,我们看到它自我学习，阅读过去的名著
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:19.91,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Mary Shelley saw her work as part of an ongoing tradition of Western literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:19.91,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,玛丽·雪莱将自己的作品视为西方文学传统的延续
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.99,0:05:23.65,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Paradise Lost, Dante, The Sorrows of Young Werther,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.99,0:05:23.65,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,《失乐园》、《神曲》、《少年维特之烦恼》
