Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.72,0:05:26.28,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,these are all directly referenced in the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.72,0:05:26.28,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这些都在书中提及
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:28.11,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,They serve as a foundation,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:28.11,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,它们作为基础
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.11,0:05:31.10,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,as key insights into the character of the Monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.11,0:05:31.10,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,是深入理解怪物形象的关键
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.10,0:05:33.82,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and they are things that the writer expects the reader
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.10,0:05:33.82,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,作者希望读者
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.83,0:05:36.41,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,to at least have a passing familiarity with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.83,0:05:36.41,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,能至少对其略知一二
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:38.70,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,That's something that would became part of the genre, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:38.70,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,这也是科幻体裁的组成部分
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.70,0:05:42.17,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Works like Hyperion are firmly grounded in that tradition,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.70,0:05:42.17,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,《海伯利安》这样的作品也扎根于这一传统
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.17,0:05:45.49,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,borrowing structure from Canterbury Tales and The Decameron,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.17,0:05:45.49,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,借鉴了《坎特伯雷故事集》和《十日谈》的结构
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:47.70,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,even taking it's name from a Keats poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:47.70,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,甚至书名就取自济慈的一首诗
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.79,0:05:49.96,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Even pieces as odd as Dhalgren
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.79,0:05:49.96,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,甚至像《戴尔格林》这样古怪的作品
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.96,0:05:53.36,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,rely on the mythological and literary tradition of the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.96,0:05:53.36,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,也要借助西方的神话和文学传统
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:57.96,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,There is an expectation in science fiction that the reader is well read.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:57.96,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,科幻作品常常默认读者博览群书
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.96,0:05:59.86,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,But there's an on-going debate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.96,0:05:59.86,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,但是人们依旧在争论
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:04.17,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,as to whether sci-fi itself is part of the classic tradition or something new,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.86,0:06:04.17,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,科幻自身到底是属于传统经典还是新的类型
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.26,0:06:08.21,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and as great works of science fiction pour in from all over the globe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.26,0:06:08.21,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,世界各地优秀的科幻作品层出不穷
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.21,0:06:09.69,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,bringing in new traditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.21,0:06:09.69,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,形成了新的传统
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:12.09,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that question becomes even more complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:12.09,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,因此这个问题变得更加复杂
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:15.05,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,But I should also mention how this tale is told.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:15.05,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,不过我还应当提一下，《弗兰肯斯坦》中的故事是如何讲述的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.05,0:06:19.42,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Through letters, relating a story told to a young man named Robert
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.05,0:06:19.42,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,一个名叫罗伯特的年轻人，写了几封信，转述了一段故事
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.42,0:06:23.31,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,by the strange and wild scientist he finds out upon the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.42,0:06:23.31,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,他在冰河上发现了一位古怪而疯狂的科学家，科学家便给他讲了这段故事
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.39,0:06:27.44,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Frankenstein is actually a story within a story within a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.39,0:06:27.44,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,《弗兰肯斯坦》实际上是一个写在书中的故事中的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.44,0:06:31.67,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,The whole work is actually an epistolary novel, although that's easy to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.44,0:06:31.67,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,整部作品实际上是一本书信体小说，尽管读者很容易忘记这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.67,0:06:33.90,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,And this allows us a juxtaposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.67,0:06:33.90,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,让我们做一个对比
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.95,0:06:38.49,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Simply by having the young Robert's story set side by side with Victor's,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.95,0:06:38.49,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,将年轻人罗伯特的故事和维克多的故事放在一起
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.49,0:06:42.98,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,as a reader, we are forced to consider the eager young explorer's ideals
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.49,0:06:42.98,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,作为读者，我们被迫思考热情的青年探险者的理想
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.02,0:06:45.70,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and, far more importantly, his motivations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.02,0:06:45.70,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,更重要的是，他的动机
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.70,0:06:48.25,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,We are forced to contrast them with Victor's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.70,0:06:48.25,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,我们被迫将他与维克多作比较
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:50.49,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,just by using this framing device,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:50.49,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.49,0:06:53.34,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Mary Shelley forces us as readers to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.49,0:06:53.34,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,玛丽·雪莱迫使我们这些读者思考
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:55.71,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,some of the ideas she wants us to consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.34,0:06:55.71,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,她想让我们思考的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:06:59.24,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,And, while we rarely see this particular framing device again,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.76,0:06:59.24,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,虽然我们之后很少再简单这样特别的“故事中的故事”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.24,0:07:02.16,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,it's important because it kicks off a long tradition
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.24,0:07:02.16,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,但是它很重要，因为这开创了一个长期的传统
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.16,0:07:04.93,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,of science fiction using framing devices,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.16,0:07:04.93,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,即科幻作品开始使用“故事中的故事”的手法
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.93,0:07:07.40,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,especially for the purpose of making us question
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.93,0:07:07.40,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,尤其是想让我们怀疑
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:10.73,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,just how reliable the central narrator really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:10.73,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,核心叙述者的可信度到底如何
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.77,0:07:12.73,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,And finally we have the title,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.77,0:07:12.73,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,最终我们有了这样的标题
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.73,0:07:14.78,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,or rather the alternate title,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.73,0:07:14.78,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,或者更确切地说，别名
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:16.52,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,The Modern Prometheus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:16.52,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,《现代普罗米修斯》
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.52,0:07:19.41,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,On the surface level, the allusion here seems clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.52,0:07:19.41,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,表面上看，这里的典故很明显
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:22.41,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Victor breathes life into inanimate flesh
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:22.41,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,维克多为死掉的肉体赋予生命
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.41,0:07:24.89,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,and he brings knowledge at great cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.41,0:07:24.89,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,以巨大代价换来知识
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.89,0:07:28.12,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,which would certainly qualify him as The Modern Prometheus
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.89,0:07:28.12,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:30.59,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,but the novel makes a point of the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:30.59,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,然而小说强调
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.59,0:07:33.34,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that he never actually shares that knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.59,0:07:33.34,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,事实上他从未分享过那些知识
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.44,0:07:37.09,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,no one ever finds out how he made his reanimated man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.44,0:07:37.09,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,没人知道他是如何使人死而复生的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.19,0:07:40.34,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,So the Prometheus label doesn't entirely fit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.19,0:07:40.34,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,所以普罗米修斯的标签并不完全贴切
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:41.72,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,But if not Victor,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:41.72,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,但是如果不是维克多
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.72,0:07:44.57,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,then who is this alternate title referring to?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.72,0:07:44.57,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,那么这个标题的别名指的是谁呢
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.70,0:07:47.16,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,It refers to the scientific method.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.70,0:07:47.16,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,其实指的是科学方法
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:50.32,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,It's this approach to the world that offers us so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:50.32,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,正是科学方法
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:52.49,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that brings mankind so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:52.49,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.49,0:07:53.79,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,but at what cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.49,0:07:53.79,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,but at what cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:56.99,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,In the end, what will be the price of such marvels?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:07:56.99,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,In the end, what will be the price of such marvels?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.07,0:08:00.58,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,We are asked this time and time again in science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.07,0:08:00.58,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,We are asked this time and time again in science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:03.23,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,it's one of sci-fi's most enduring themes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:03.23,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,it's one of sci-fi's most enduring themes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.23,0:08:05.59,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,From the Martian Chronicles, to Pump 6,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.23,0:08:05.59,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,From the Martian Chronicles, to Pump 6,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.59,0:08:07.07,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Terminator, to the Matrix,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.59,0:08:07.07,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,Terminator, to the Matrix,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.08,0:08:09.42,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,we see it again and again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.08,0:08:09.42,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,we see it again and again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:10.96,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,And I think It's important to note,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:10.96,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,And I think It's important to note,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:13.72,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,the alternate title isn't The New Icarus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.96,0:08:13.72,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,the alternate title isn't The New Icarus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:17.02,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,Prometheus's story isn't a flew too close to the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:17.02,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,Prometheus's story isn't a flew too close to the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:19.59,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,brought about your own destruction cautionary tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.02,0:08:19.59,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,brought about your own destruction cautionary tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:21.08,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,In Prometheus's story,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:21.08,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,In Prometheus's story,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.08,0:08:22.82,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,he does suffer for his actions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.08,0:08:22.82,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,he does suffer for his actions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.82,0:08:25.52,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,but his sacrifice benefits us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.82,0:08:25.52,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,but his sacrifice benefits us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:28.22,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,The greatest good comes through that sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:28.22,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,The greatest good comes through that sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:30.68,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,These books, these works of art
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:30.68,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,These books, these works of art
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.68,0:08:34.36,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,that examine the farthest edge of where our science might lead us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.68,0:08:34.36,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,that examine the farthest edge of where our science might lead us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:36.11,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,can be cautionary tales
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:36.11,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,can be cautionary tales
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.11,0:08:39.20,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,while simultaneously celebrating science,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.11,0:08:39.20,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,while simultaneously celebrating science,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:42.89,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,daring us to push ahead as far and as fast as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:42.89,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,daring us to push ahead as far and as fast as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.89,0:08:47.05,ExtraSciFi - EN,,0,0,0,,while, at the same time, urging us to be wiser than their protagonists.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.89,0:08:47.05,ExtraSciFi - 中文,,0,0,0,,while, at the same time, urging us to be wiser than their protagonists.
